componentDescription: A flexible container that allows users to resize its content areas by dragging adjustable dividers.

children.description: Defines the content to be rendered within the Resizable component.

orientation.description: Specifies the orientation of the resizable panels (e.g., horizontal or vertical).

size.description: Determines the overall size behavior or initial size of the resizable component.

variant.description: Defines the visual style or behavior variant of the resizable component.

defaultSizes.description: Sets the initial sizes for the resizable panels.

onSizesChange.description: Callback function triggered when the sizes of the panels change.

minSize.description: Specifies the minimum size allowed for any panel.

maxSize.description: Specifies the maximum size allowed for any panel.

collapsible.description: Enables or disables the ability for panels to collapse.

autoSaveId.description: An identifier used to automatically save and restore panel sizes.

storage.description: Custom storage mechanism for saving and restoring panel states.

keyboardResizeBy.description: Defines the increment for resizing panels using keyboard interactions.

views.description: Provides custom styles for different parts of the Resizable component.
